This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with semantic matching in long text. Additionally, the use of neural networks and prior knowledge suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The focus on matching and retrieval also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR). Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks and multilayer perceptrons suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
